{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.41",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 41,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 41",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 41 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:1",
      "text": "I will not stir him up, like one that is cruel, for who can resist my countenance?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:2",
      "text": "Who hath given me before that I should repay him? All things that are under heaven are mine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:3",
      "text": "I will not spare him, nor his mighty words, and framed to make supplication.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:4",
      "text": "Who can discover the face of his garment? or who can go into the midst of his mouth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:5",
      "text": "Who can open the doors of his face? his teeth are terrible round about.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:6",
      "text": "His body is like molten shields, shut close up with scales pressing upon one another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:7",
      "text": "One is joined to another, and not so much as any air can come between them:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:8",
      "text": "They stick one to another and they hold one another fast, and shall not be separated.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:9",
      "text": "His sneezing is like the shining of fire, and his eyes like the eyelids of the morning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:10",
      "text": "Out of his mouth go forth lamps, like torches of lighted fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:11",
      "text": "Out of his nostrils goeth smoke, like that of a pot heated and boiling.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:12",
      "text": "His breath kindleth coals, and a flame cometh forth out of his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:13",
      "text": "In his neck strength shall dwell, and want goeth before his face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:14",
      "text": "The members of his flesh cleave one to another: he shall send lightnings against him, and they shall not be carried to another place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:15",
      "text": "His heart shall be as hard as a stone, and as firm as a smith's anvil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:16",
      "text": "When he shall raise him up, the angels shall fear, and being affrighted shall purify themselves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:17",
      "text": "When a sword shall lay at him, it shall not be able to hold, nor a spear, nor a breastplate.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:18",
      "text": "For he shall esteem iron as straw, and brass as rotten wood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:19",
      "text": "The archer shall not put him to flight, the stones of the sling are to him like stubble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:20",
      "text": "As stubble will he esteem the hammer, and he will laugh him to scorn who shaketh the spear.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:21",
      "text": "The beams of the sun shall be under him, and he shall strew gold under him like mire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:22",
      "text": "He shall make the deep sea to boil like a pot, and shall make it as when ointments boil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:23",
      "text": "A path shall shine after him, he shall esteem the deep as growing old.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:24",
      "text": "There is no power upon earth that can be compared with him who was made to fear no one.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.41.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:25",
      "text": "He beholdeth every high thing, he is king over all the children of pride.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
